Route 53 - Hosted zones in AWS ?

Route 53 — DNS service
→ Private & public hosted and configured inside route 53


Hosted zones = Containers holding DNS records for a domain example.com ( a record , CNAME , MX records )

 → Public Hosted zone = lets the public look up the DNS records for a domain + can query this if needed ( if u want your domain visible )

 → Private Hosted zone = normally in a VPC where you can’t look up the DNS records for a domain ( internal service that you don’t want exposed 
     ( if u don’t your domain visible )

Same price for private / public zones 0.50p
Route 53 available and scalable




Public vs Private hosted zones in AWS? 

Create a Public Hosted zone  = when you want IP to accessible over internet
 -> public facing and internet facing

Create Private Hosted zone = when you want IP to be internally accessible and when dealing with a virtual private network (VPC)
-> private facing and internal 




